<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Budget Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503104894 Tehran IRNA in English 1023 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, March 15, IRNA -- The Council of Guardians 
here Tuesday approved the next year budget bill as not being 
contradictory with the Islamic principles and the Iranian 
Constitution. The Council's public relations office said that 
the council had studied the bill in several extra meetings. 
  The Majlis made the amendments to the points which the 
Council referred to as incorrect twice. The Council of 
Guardians in its Tuesday morning session announced its final 
approval with the next year budget bill, the office added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

