<H3> <TI>   Syria's Al-Shar' Voices Concern About Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503200994 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' at the </F>
airport in Algiers upon his arrival on 15 March -- recorded] 
  [Text] I have been assigned by President Hafiz al-Asad to 
convey a message to his brother President Liamine Zeroual and to 
listen to whatever President Zeroual wants to tell us about the 
situation in dear Algeria. Undoubtedly, we in Syria are very 
concerned and worried about what is taking place here out of our 
concern for Algeria's unity and its role in the Arab and Islamic 
arenas, and on the basis of our conviction that President 
Zeroual's statement on the dialogue was positive and it is bound 
to lead to the easing of the brotherly people's suffering and to 
the establishment of security and stability in this country. 

</TEXT>

