<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resistance Attacks Israeli Patrol in South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503170594 Paris AFP in English 1652 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1503170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sidon, March 15 (AFP)--Iranian-backed guerrillas 
ambushed an Israeli army patrol in occupied south Lebanon on 
Tuesday [15 March], provoking retaliatory shelling, security 
services said. 
  The Islamic Resistance, Hizballah's armed wing, said "a 
Merkava tank exploded and a truck fell into the valley in 
flames" in the attack at the entrance to al-Shaqif Castle in 
Israel's self-declared security zone. 
  Lebanese security services confirmed the attack but could 
provide no information on eventual casualties. 
  Israeli tanks and artillery then shelled woods and the area 
around villages opposite the Crusader-era castle while Israeli 
helicopter gunships machinegunned targets in the region, police 
said. 
  There were no immediate reports of casualties following the 
Israeli attacks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

