<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Attacks Israeli Patrol in 'Arnun </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503210394 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 2015 GMT 15 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1503210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This evening resistance men attacked an Israeli 
patrol in 'Arnun, on the edge of the occupied border strip. 
Following that, Israeli forces shelled the al-Hamra farm and 
the area around Qal'at al-Shaqif, where the resistance has 
positions, using 155-mm shells, as our correspondent in the 
south reported. The Israeli shelling was accompanied by 
warplane and helicopter overflights of the region; the planes 
dropped flares. Two Israeli helicopters raked the valleys of 
the al-Hamra farm and the area near the attack, for which 
Hizballah claimed responsibility. There were no reports of 
casualties. 
  Earlier, Israeli forces sporadically shelled the hills of 
Iqlim al-Tuffah, particularly Jabal Safi, Luwayzah, Mlita, and 
Sujud. 

</TEXT>

