<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Marks International Jerusalem Day </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1103141194 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1230 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1103141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hizballah has staged a rally in Beirut's Southern 
Suburb to mark the International Jerusalem Day. Speaking at the 
rally, Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah stressed the 
importance of the struggle to liberate Jerusalem and the need to 
confront the Zionist enemy's attempt to Judaize the holy places. 
He also demanded Lebanon's withdrawal from the peace 
negotiations. 
  Mass marches were held in the suburb's streets, carrying 
banners denouncing Israel and its aggressive practices. 

</TEXT>

