<H3> <TI>   Official Leaves To Open Bank Branch in West Bank </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1603131094 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 
16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1603131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fayiz Abu-al-'Aynayn, director general of the Bank 
of Jordan, left Amman today for the occupied Arab territories to 
supervise the opening of the bank's first branch in Ramallah. 
  Muhammad 'Ali Ibrahim, the bank's assistant director 
general, 
said that work in this bank, which has been properly equipped 
and staffed with employees, will begin next week. He noted that 
the branch will open after it receives the approval of Jordan 
Central Bank. He added that the bank will open other branches 
in Nabulus, Hebron, Janin, Tulkarm, Jericho, Bethlehem, and Gaza 
after they are proven economically feasible and are approved by 
Jordan Central Bank. 

