<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hebron Dignitaries Ask Shahaq To Lift Curfew </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1503180894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 15 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1503180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Senior IDF [Israel Defense Forces] officers, 
including the deputy chief of staff, the coordinator of 
activities in the territories, the commander of IDF troops and 
the head of the Civil Administration in Judaea and Samaria, 
conferred this afternoon with Hebron dignitaries, including the 
mayor and members of the Chamber of Commerce. 
  Muhyi-al-Din Nimr, the spokesman of the Chamber of Commerce, 
told our correspondent Moti Amir that the dignitaries asked the 
officers to lift the curfew on the city and to allow the 
residents to return to work and resume normal life. According 
to Nimr, Major General Shahaq voiced his sorrow over the 
massacre in Hebron, and said he knew that the enemies of peace 
had become stronger as a result of this deed. Shahaq pointed 
out that after the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho agreement 
it will also be Hebron's turn to attain Palestinian self-rule. 
  The dignitaries asked the IDF officers to reduce the 
friction 
between IDF troops and the local population in order to avert 
confrontations and riots once the curfew is lifted. 

</TEXT>

