<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Leaves for New York via Amman 15 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1503164294 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1600 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1503164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz left 
Amman for New York today for talks with UN officials on 
monitoring Iraqi weapons and the economic embargo imposed on 
Iraq. 
  'Aziz arrived in Amman yesterday en route to New York. He 
was received and seen off by Dr. Said al-Tall, deputy prime 
minister and minister of higher education. [passage omitted on 
expected Security Council meetings] 

</TEXT>

