<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Aziz To Begin Talks 16 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1603110794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1015 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1603110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The United Nations, 16 Mar (INA)--This afternoon, 
Baghdad time, Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz will begin 
contacts with officials of the United Nations and the UN 
Security Council. 
  The deputy prime minister has arrived in New York on a visit 
to the United Nations for talks on the need for the UN Security 
Council to honor its commitments as enshrined in Paragraph 22 of 
Resolution 687, which provide for lifting the sanctions clamped 
on Iraq. 
  Tariq 'Aziz will hold his first meeting with Jean-Bernard 
Merimee, the French ambassador to the United Nations and 
president of the UN Security Council, this afternoon. He will 
also meet with the representatives of several permanent and 
nonpermanent members of the UN Security Council. 
  During his visit to the United Nations, the deputy prime 
minister will hold talks with UNSC members and with UN Secretary 
General Dr. Butrus Ghali. 
  Tariq 'Aziz is accompanied on the visit by an Iraqi 
delegation comprised of Lieutenant General Engineer 'Amir 
Muhammad Rashid, director of the Military Industrialization 
Organization; Dr. Riyad al-Qaysi, under secretary of the Foreign 
Ministry; and several Iraqi experts. 

</TEXT>

