<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arrest of Army Officers `Continuing' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1503165094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 15 Mar 94 p5 </F>
<F P=103> PM1503165094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- An informed Iraqi source 
has stated that the arrest of army officers is still continuing, 
five months after the announcement of the latest abortive 
attempt to overthrow the regime. 
  The source said that the detainees include 8th Division 
Commander Staff Brigadier General Salah al-Juburi and a number 
of middle-ranking officers and retired officers. 
  A system for the control of retired officers has enabled the 
Iraqi Government to impose a procedure on them under which they 
have to report daily and sign the registers at military 
industrialization offices and Olympic Committee offices where 
they have to appear nominally for work every day, and under 
which they are not allowed to leave Baghdad or Iraq. This 
system is supervised by 'Udayy Saddam Husayn, son of the Iraqi 
president, a responsibility previously shared with him by Husayn 
Kamil al-Majid, who has been forced by illness to stay home. 
  Meanwhile, a state of alert continues for the fifth day at 
the entrances to and in the main streets of the capital where 
cars are searched and the identities of passengers and 
pedestrians are checked. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

