<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Details of Arrests Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1503200594 (Clandestine) Voice of Rebellious Iraq in 
Arabic 1800 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1503200594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Rebellious Iraq </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The regime continues to be frightened of a possible 
military coup by officers who oppose the hated regime after the 
failure of two coups by senior officers in July and August last 
year. Our informed sources in Baghdad say that tyrant Saddam 
has retired more Army officers, who will be on their way to 
disappearing from the scene forever. The source said that the 
following officers have been retired: 
  1. Brigadier General Baha al-Din Sami; 
  2. Brigadier General Malik al-Juburi from the Republican 
Guard; 
  3. Brigadier General 'Abd-al-Rahman from the second police 
force [al-shurtah al-thaniyah]; 
  4. Colonel Husam 'Abd-al-Razzaq al-'Ubaydi from the 
Republican Guard; 
  5. Staff Colonel Nazim Saddam al-Rubay'i from the 2d Tank 
Battalion. 
  A few days ago, the special security forces launched a 
large-scale arrest campaign among Army officers because the 
criminal regime suspects they had secret contacts with groups 
and cells of officers working to topple the Saddamist regime. 
The campaign concentrated on officers from Baghdad city and the 
Mosul governorate. 

</TEXT>

