<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamic Council Urges Boycott of Hebron Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303180994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 13 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Higher Islamic Council in East Jerusalem has 
called on the Muslim residents of Hebron to boycott the state 
commission of inquiry into the massacre at the Tomb of the 
Patriarchs. The Council rejected cooperation with a 
state-appointed commission on any issue pertaining to the holy 
places. 
  Our Arab affairs correspondent Arye Gus has learned that the 
decision to boycott the Shamgar commission was inspired by 
Jordan, and contravenes the Waqf's initial position in support 
of testifying before the commission. 
  Several days ago, the Hebron Municipality published a 
proclamation calling for the expulsion of the Jewish settlers 
from Hebron, the dismantlement of Qiryat Arba' and the other 
settlements, and the lifting of the closure from the town. The 
Municipality, which was appointed at the time by the Military 
Government, also demands the removal of the Jewish synagogue 
from the Tomb of the Patriarchs and the restoration of the 
site's Islamic nature. 

</TEXT>

