<F P=100> Western Sahara </F>
<H3> <TI>   Polisario Rejects 2 of 3 Options Proposed by UN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503224394 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in French 1800 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503224394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Polisario Front has rejected options A and C of 
the report of the UN secretary-general presented yesterday to 
the UN Security Council to break the deadlock in the peace 
process in Western Sahara. The first option -- option A -- 
concerns the organization of a referendum of self-determination 
next December without taking into account the reservations 
voiced by the Polisario Front. The third option -- option C -- 
is the pure and simple withdrawal of the UN. This, according to 
sources close to the Polisario, marks the failure of the United 
Nations and can only lead to the escalation of the conflict and 
war. As for option B, it envisages the continuation of 
negotiations as from 30 June in an attempt to secure the 
agreement of the two parties -- that is, Morocco and the 
Polisario -- on the criteria of identification of electors 
illegible to vote. The Polisario Front voiced reservations on 
these options [A and C] as explained by the ambassador of 
Western Sahara to Algiers: 
  [Begin recording] [Ambassador] The Saharans think that these 
options need to be amended, that is the commission of 
identification of voters should be linked to the so-called 
compromise proposed by Butrus Butrus-Ghali. We think that this 
compromise is the formulation of the concessions made by our 
side. The UN Security Council should thus take into account the 
reservations voiced by the Polisario Front, included in the 
memorandum addressed to the UN special representative on 25 
February. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-13586 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes051_c_94001" </HT>


