<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prince Hasan, Croatian President Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1503061594 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1503061594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News at Ten" program] </F>
  [Text] His Royal Highness Crown Prince Hasan met Croatian 
President Franjo Tudjman after he arrived in Zagreb on a brief 
visit. Besides his meeting with the Croatian leader, Prince 
Hasan will inspect the Jordanian United Nations peacekeeping 
force in the former Yugoslav Republic, which has recently been 
beefed up. 
  The commander of the Jordanian UN contingent, who is also a 
head of the UN peacekeeping mission, Ghazi al-Tayyib, and senior 
officers received the crown prince. 
  His royal highness is accompanied by His Royal Highness 
Prince 'Abdallah Bin-al-Husayn and Minister of State for Foreign 
Affairs Talal al-Hasan. 
  The Crown Prince told reporters he was glad to have a second 
opportunity to discuss with Tudjman efforts aimed at peace in 
former Yugoslavia: 
  [Begin Hasan recording, in progress]...discussed with 
President Tudjman at the gracious reception the ongoing 
developments in the region. I would like to say how gratified 
we are to see progress in the ongoing talks in Vienna. We are 
deeply interested in the concept of a bicommunal community as a 
first step leading to further cooperation between Croatia and 
the Bosnian Muslims. And I certainly would like to say that the 
containment of violence is very much the role to which, we, 
through the United Nations, have committed ourselves to. [end 
recording] 
  Prince Hasan also met the UN secretary general's personal 
representative in former Yugoslavia, Yasushi Akashi, and 
discussed the UN peacekeeping operation. 
  The crown prince left Amman earlier in the day on a two-day 
visit and was seen off by senior officials. 

</TEXT>

