<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Hasan Returns From Croatia, Bosnia Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1703073694 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 2100 GMT 
16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1703073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, minister of state for 
foreign affairs, returned to Amman this evening after 
accompanying His Highness Crown Prince Hasan during his visit to 
Croatia and Bosnia. 
  The minister spoke about His Highness Crown Prince Hasan's 
visit and his meeting with Jordanian troops taking part in the 
UN peace-keeping forces stationed in Croatia and Bosnia. He 
said that the objective of this visit was to hold a series of 
meetings with Croatian and Bosnian leaders and to meet with the 
Jordanian officers, NCOs, and troops taking part in the 
peacekeeping forces in Croatia and Bosnia. The visit was also 
aimed at meeting with the commanders of the UN forces in the 
former Yugoslavia. 
  He said that this visit comes within the framework of 
supporting ongoing international peace efforts and the recent 
agreement reached between the Croatians and Bosnians in Vienna 
aimed at ending the conflict, achieving peace, and closing a 
chapter of history full of tribulations and sufferings. 
  Al-Hasan noted that the visit added a new dimension to the 
credibility of Jordan and its leader His Majesty King Husayn. 
The visit also highlighted the respect the leadership and 
people of these countries have for Jordan and its leader His 
Majesty King Husayn and his effective contribution in support of 
international efforts and the United Nations' role through the 
participation of Jordanian troops. Jordan has the second 
largest contingent, after France, of peace-keeping forces in the 
region. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

