<H3> <TI>   INA Notes French Officials' Remarks on Ekeus, Iraq </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1603202894 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1900 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1603202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] INA has learned that France wants to change Rolf 
Ekeus, chairman of the UN Special Commission. High-level 
diplomatic sources told INA that French Ambassador Jean-Bernard 
Merimee met with the nonaligned states' ambassadors at the UN 
Security Council yesterday afternoon and discussed with them the 
UN Security Council's relations with Iraq. He told the 
ambassadors: Yes, Ekeus is a gentle, diplomatic, and diligent 
person, but, frankly speaking, I say to you that Ekeus must be 
changed as the Special Commission chairman because his actions 
depend on one viewpoint, which is the U.S. viewpoint, without 
taking into consideration the viewpoints of the other states at 
the UN Security Council. 
  The INA correspondent has verified the French Ambassador's 
remarks from other diplomatic sources that took part in 
yesterday's meeting. 

</TEXT>

