<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Sends Message to Clinton on Peace Process </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603153094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1430 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1603153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 16 Mar (MENA)--Palestinian President Yasir 
'Arafat has asked U.S. President Bill Clinton to exert efforts 
and use his influence to save the peace process, which has been 
deadlocked since the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre in Hebron in 
the middle of the month of Ramadan. The request came in a 
message that 'Arafat sent to Clinton. 
  The Palestinian news agency said today the message dealt 
with 
the difficulties blocking a Security Council resolution 
denouncing the massacre and providing international protection 
for the Palestinian people in the occupied territories and their 
holy places. 
  The message also dealt with Israeli maneuvers and lies aimed 
at blocking the implementation of the Declaration of Principles 
and the serious situation in the occupied land. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

