<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clinton Remarks on Jerusalem Spark Reaction </TI></H3>
<H4>   Qaddumi Offers Response </H4>
<F P=102> NC1703071094 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0615 GMT 17 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703071094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on 
Peres' remarks that Israel accepts taking some measures in 
Hebron after the PLO agrees to return to the negotiations, Faruq 
Qaddumi, the head of the PLO Political Department, has stated 
that the Palestinian leadership does not trust promises by 
Israeli officials. Peres has already made many unfulfilled 
promises. 
  In a statement to AL-HAYAH [no date as heard], Qaddumi 
revealed that the Palestinian leadership has rejected an Israeli 
request to hold a meeting between Peres and 'Arafat in 
Washington. 
  Responding to Israeli press reports yesterday that U.S. 
President Bill Clinton wants to announce that Jerusalem is the 
capital of Israel, Qaddumi said: If this happens, we say the 
peace process is over. He added: If this is confirmed, we will 
withdraw from the negotiations, because Washington would be 
violating the basis on which these negotiations were started. 
Qaddumi said he expects things to drag on before the 
negotiations are resumed, because Israel is procrastinating, 
playing for time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

