<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clinton Remarks on Jerusalem Spark Reaction </TI></H3>
<H4>   PNC Secretary: Remarks Raise `Fears' </H4>
<F P=102> NC1603121294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1124 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1603121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 16 Mar (MENA)--Palestine National Council 
[PNC] Secretary Muhammad Subayh has denounced U.S. President 
Clinton's recent remarks that Jerusalem is Israel's united 
capital. 
  In an exclusive statement to MENA, Subayh said that such 
remarks contradict every official position espoused by former 
U.S. Presidents and the U.S. commitment to the UN Security 
Council that holy Jerusalem is an occupied territory. 
  He added: The Palestinian people and all the peoples of the 
Islamic nation are astonished and denounce the U.S. President's 
remarks, which come on the heels of the al-Ibrahimi Mosque 
massacre. These remarks raise fears about U.S. credibility and 
commitment to the peace operation. 
  Subayh noted that these remarks show total bias toward 
Israel, violate international law and UN and Security Council 
resolutions, and provoke the feelings of faithful Muslims and 
Christians worldwide, who can never accept the Judaization of 
this holy city. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

