<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Musa, Palestinian Envoy on UN Meeting on Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503160894 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1503160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has said that Egypt is 
holding consultations with the parties concerned with the Middle 
East peace process as well as with UN Security Council members. 
The subject of the consultations is the holding of a Security 
Council session to discuss the attack against worshipers at the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque and the passing of a resolution condemning 
the massacre. 
  Palestinian Ambassador to Cairo Sa'id Kamal said that 
Minister 'Amr Musa today gave him an urgent message for 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat concerning the consultations 
Egypt is holding on a UN Security Council meeting to denounce 
the massacre. 
  The Palestinian envoy said that the Palestinians are 
unwavering in their call for the condemnation of the atrocity 
committed by the settlers against the Palestinian people and for 
international protection of the Palestinian people living in the 
occupied territories. Ambassador Kamal said that Palestinian 
and Egyptian consultations are continuing to achieve this end. 

</TEXT>

