<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Calls for Settlers' Withdrawal Temetable </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603191194 Paris AFP in English 1816 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1603191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman, March 16 (AFP)--A senior PLO official 
Wednesday [16 March] called for a timetable for evacuating 
Jewish settlers from the occupied territories. 
  Bassam Abu-Sharif, political adviser to PLO Chairman Yasir 
'Arafat, said the settlers in the occupied West Bank and Gaza 
Strip "are an integral part of the Israeli occupation, and that 
is why it is necessary to set a timetable for their evacuation 
in parallel with the withdrawal of regular forces." 
  If the Israeli Government really wanted peace, Abu-Sharif 
said, "it must go ahead with such an evacuation." 
  The PLO demanded the dismantling of certain flashpoint 
settlements in the occupied territories following the February 
25 massacre of Arab worshippers in a Hebron mosque by a Jewish 
settler, Barukh Goldstein. 
  Abu-Sharif said the United States financed the construction 
of the Jewish settlements, and should "finance their evacuation 
as they did for the settlements in the Sinai desert," which was 
returned to Egypt. 
  He reiterated the PLO's refusal to resume peace talks with 
Israel until the United Nations "assumes its total 
responsibility for protecting the Palestinian people in the 
occupied territories." 
  The UN Security Council is due to vote Friday on a draft 
resolution on the occupied territories. 
  The PLO has called for the deployment of an international 
protection force in the territories. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

