<F P=100> Lebanon </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Directorate Issues Statement on Explosives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603174494 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1630 GMT 16 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1603174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Unverified reports today about the defusing of 
explosive devices in certain quarters aroused panic among the 
citizens. To clarify the truth, the Internal Security Forces 
General Directorate issued the following statement: 
  Investigations into the discovery of a 60-mm mortar shell in 
the playground of the Assiriac al-Taraqqi School in Burj Hammud, 
al-Nab'ah, discovered that the shell was not primed for 
detonation. 
  Regarding the shell found in the 'Abd-al-Qadir Lecee School 
in the patriarchate locality, the statement said that a 
rocket-propelled grenade round was found on the roof of the 
school's laboratory. A military expert removed it and 
determined that it was an old remnant of the war. 

</TEXT>

