<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Egypt Puts Quotas on Maghreb Pilgrims </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703110694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0600 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Egyptian authorities have decided that they will 
allow only 2,000 Algerian pilgrims to cross their territory by 
land this year on their way to the holy places. Last year, 
nearly 24,000 pilgrims travelled by road to perform the annual 
pilgrimage. 
  According to information available to us, the Egyptian 
authorities have demanded that these Algerian pilgrims travel on 
coaches laid on by tourist agencies and not by private 
transport, as has been the practice so far. This decision, 
which applies to all nationals from the Arab Maghreb, is 
believed to be due to security considerations. 

</TEXT>

