<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres on Talks With Syria, Security in Hebron </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1603174894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 GMT 16 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1603174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres says Israel knows 
that negotiations with Syria are a top priority now, and it is 
ready for them. Speaking to foreign correspondents in 
Jerusalem, Peres said Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin would 
investigate ways of advancing peace talks with Damascus when he 
meets in Washington this evening with U.S. President Bill 
Clinton. 
  On talks with the PLO, Peres said Israel could not agree to 
Palestinian demands for the removal of Jewish settlers from 
Hebron. But, he added, Israel would take additional steps in 
Hebron to meet Palestinian security concerns. He did not 
elaborate. 

</TEXT>

