<H3> <TI>   New IDF Outpost in Qiryat Arba'; 13 Wounded in Strip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1603181894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 16 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1603181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thirteen local residents were wounded as soldiers 
fired on rioters in Jabalyah in the Gaza Strip. In Janin, a 
Molotov cocktail was hurled at a Border Police patrol. Our 
correspondent Moti Amir reports that the policemen gave chase 
and detained the thrower, who had another Molotov cocktail in 
his possession. 
  [Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew at 1500 GMT on 16 March adds: 
"Palestinian students in Judaea, Samaria, and Gaza today went 
back to school, after an extended interval which started after 
the Hebron massacre. In Hebron, students were prevented from 
going back to school by the ongoing curfew." 
  [The report further states that "a young Arab woman armed 
with a knife today attempted to stab soldiers near the Ramallah 
Police building. One of the soldiers fired at the assailant's 
feet. She was wounded and taken in for questioning."] 
  The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] has started building an 
outpost in Qiryat Arba' designed to enhance settlers' security. 
The outpost will be situated on the Qiryat Arba' municipal land 
between Qiryat Arba' and the Giv'at Haharsina neighborhood. Our 
correspondent notes that the construction of the outpost is 
being done in concert and coordination with Qiryat Arba' leaders. 

</TEXT>

