<H3> <TI>   IDF Completes Evacuation of First Base in Gaza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1703092794 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 17 Mar 94 p 
3 </F>

<F P=103> TA1703092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by David Regev and military correspondent Arye </F>
Kiesel] 
  [Excerpts] For the first time in the Gaza Strip -- and for 
the first time since the signing of the Israeli-PLO Declaration 
of Principles -- the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] yesterday 
evacuated a whole military base from Gaza's Rimal neighborhood. 
The vacated area went back to the residents of the 
neighborhood. Confirming the report, official military sources 
noted that the evacuation came as part of the redeployment of 
troops in the Gaza Strip. [passage omitted] 
  Military correspondent Arye Kiesel adds: The evacuation of 
the base yesterday came after Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin gave 
his consent to begin a real evacuation from the Gaza Strip. A 
senior military source in the Southern Command said yesterday: 
"We are done with `thinning out the fat' from the Gaza Strip. 
The work was done in accordance with the operational order 
concerning a redeployment in the Gaza Strip and Jericho, and 
regardless of the massacre in Hebron." 
  Defense establishment sources voiced their assessment 
yesterday that the prime minister had given his consent for two 
reasons: First, as a public gesture to the inhabitants of the 
Gaza Strip and Fatah members there; second, to enable the IDF to 
carry out a rapid evacuation in the event that the peace talks 
resume and an agreement is reached on the beginning of the 
evacuation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

