<H3> <TI>   Source on Fatah Delegation's Visit to Knesset </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503221394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2130 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1503221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 15 Mar (MENA)--An official Palestinian source 
said tonight that the Fatah delegation that visited the Israeli 
Knesset today consisted of Arabs from inside the occupied 
territories and was led by lawyer Ziyyad Abu-Zayyad. 
  The source said the delegation had a dialogue with an 
Israeli 
Labor Party delegation led by Ya'el Dayan, the party's official 
spokesman, with a view to ending the current crisis faced by the 
peace negotiations. 
  The source said that members of the Palestinian delegation 
stressed that peace and settlements do not go together, and 
Israel must realize that the PLO postponed the peace talks 
because of the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. 
  The Israeli Labor Party, led by Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin, 
had invited the Palestinian delegation to visit the Knesset. 

