<H3> <TI>   Editorial Views Clinton Remarks on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1603165994 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 15 Mar 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> TA1603165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "Jerusalem"] </F>
  [Text] President Clinton's remarks about Jerusalem are 
particularly noteworthy, although they would have sounded better 
had they not been said in the context of the UN Security Council 
resolution that is expected to mention East Jerusalem as 
occupied territory. We have to wait and see if and how the 
President's commitment to a united Jerusalem as the capital of 
Israel is translated into the vote of his UN delegation. 
  And, lest we forget the forum in which the remarks were 
made: 
The leaders of the Jewish community in the United States -- the 
same people whose lobbying and donations we so much like to 
dismiss -- are the ones who heard from the President his renewed 
commitment to the issue of Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

