<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives Russian, Egyptian Envoys </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603181494 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The brother president leader Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 
'Arafat] last night received the special envoy of Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin, who delivered to him a message from the 
Russian leadership on the results of the Vladivostok meeting 
that was held on Monday between Andrey Kozyrev, Russian foreign 
affairs minister, and Warren Christopher, U.S. secretary of 
state. 
  During the meeting, the recent developments and contacts 
currently under way at the UN Security Council for issuing a 
resolution on the massacre in the holy al-Ibrahimi Mosque in 
Hebron in the occupied West Bank were reviewed. [passage omitted] 
  The brother president leader Abu-'Ammar also received 
yesterday afternoon Ibrahim 'Allam, ambassador of the Arab 
Republic of Egypt in Tunis. 
  The Egyptian ambassador delivered to brother Abu-'Ammar a 
message from the Egyptian leadership on the recent developments 
of the peace process in the Middle East and the consultations 
and contacts currently under way at the different levels. 

</TEXT>

