<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Calls for Elections `Within 3 Months' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1603200794 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 16 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1603200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of the 
state of Palestine and chairman of the PLO Executive Committee, 
has stressed the need to hold elections in the occupied 
territories within three months, adding that this depends on 
Israel's approval. 
  In a statement to DPA broadcast yesterday, President 
Abu-'Ammar urged the Security Council to quickly adopt a 
resolution condemning the massacre, which claimed the lives of a 
number of Palestinian worshipers in the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in 
the occupied West Bank city of Hebron. 
  Brother Abu-'Ammar said providing security for the 
frightened 
and infuriated sons of the homeland in the occupied territories 
is more important than other issues. Brother President 
Abu-'Ammar described Israel's refusal to renegotiate the already 
signed agreements as an attempt to gain time. He added that the 
Israelis are playing tactical games and are not willing to 
provide anything tangible. 

</TEXT>

