<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shabwah Governor, Security Director Ordered To Leave </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603191794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1800 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1603191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 16 Mar (MENA)--It was learned here today that 
the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP], one of the ruling coalition 
parties in Yemen, used tanks and artillery in the Shabwah 
Governorate, one of the southern governorates, to surround the 
governorate headquarters and the Security Directorate 
headquarters to force Governor Dirham 'Abduh Nu'man, member of 
the General People's Congress General Committee, and Colonel 
Ahmad 'Ali Muhsin, the governorate security director and leading 
member of the General People's Congress in the governorate, to 
leave the governorate immediately. 
  The governor and the security director received from the 
military commander, who belongs to the YSP led by 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid, and the YSP secretary in the governorate an urgent 
ultimatum to immediately leave their workplace in the 
governorate or they would be driven out by military force. It 
is worth noting that President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih is the 
General People's Congress secretary general in Yemen. 

</TEXT>

