<H3> <TI>   Membership of Subjects Denied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1803073594 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0545 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1803073594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source in the Lebanese Forces has 
commented on the statement issued by the General Directorate of 
the Internal Security Forces on the arrest of Faris Philip 
al-Hajj and Nabil (Krikorian) as follows: 
  The Lebanese Forces would like to point out the following: 
  1. Around 150,000 personnel joined the Lebanese Forces 
departments between 1977 and 1991, the year the militias were 
disbanded. The Lebanese Forces have no proof that the two 
suspects joined any of its administrative departments. 
  2. The Lebanese Forces started to keep records of its 
personnel in 1981 but these two names have appeared in none of 
the Forces' records. So the Lebanese Forces categorically deny 
that the two suspects have been among its members at any time 
since 1981. 
  The Forces strongly condemn the crimes committed by the two, 
including plunder, robbery, and assault against a clergyman, and 
calls on the Lebanese judiciary to hand down the maximum 
punishment on them and on others who commit similar acts, even 
Lebanese Forces members. The Lebanese Forces would like to draw 
the public's attention to some malicious campaigns that seek to 
serve political goals that are known to everybody. 

</TEXT>

