<F P=102>  PM1603144694 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 16 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1603144694 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Al-Kikhya's Wife Sends Letter to </F>
al-Qadhdhafi: I Am Certain You Will Find Him and Return Him to 
Us Free"] 
  [Excerpt] London, AL-HAYAH -- Mrs. Baha' al-'Amri, wife of 
former Libyan Foreign Minister Mansur al-Kikhya, sent a letter 
to Libyan leader Colonel Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi dated 10/4/1994 
[as published], appealing to him to "find him and return him 
free to his children and home." 
  The letter, a copy of which AL-HAYAH has received, said: "In 
the name of freedom of democracy I writing to you to ask about 
the fate of the Libyan citizen Mansur al-Kikhya, my husband and 
the father of my children and a respectable man who was abducted 
from Egyptian territory. I understand from your recent speech 
that you are seeking to find him because he is a human rights 
case." She went on: "Three months have elapsed and we do not 
know who committed this ugly crime. Maybe cowardly elements 
did, and I am certain that your hands will reach them and that 
you will punish these cowardly people." 
  She also pointed out that Libya "does not wish to lose a 
free 
and noble man who believes in nothing except right, peace, and 
dialogue..., and I am certain that you will find him and return 
him free to his children and home.... You will find him 
anywhere, inside or outside Libya...it does not matter...what 
matters is for him to come back to his children, who have not 
stopped crying." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

