<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Promises to SHAS Mentor Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1703193594 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1800 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1703193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israel will not agree to reopen the Oslo and Cairo 
agreements. This transpires from Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin's 
letter to Rabbi 'Ovadya Yosef. Our party affairs correspondent 
Yaron Deqel obtained a version of the letter, which paved the 
way for SHAS' [Torah Observing Sephardim] return to the 
government. These are the four points that Rabin promised SHAS: 
The Declaration of Principles with the Palestinians and the 
Cairo agreement will not be reopened for negotiations; Jerusalem 
will remain the united capital of Israel and under complete 
Israeli sovereignty. Rabin also promised Rabbi Yosef not to 
compromise with the Palestinians on the right of return, except 
for cases of family reunification, and that any peace agreement 
involving a return of territory will be brought for a public 
decision by means of a referendum or elections. 
  Rafi Edri, who is directing the negotiations with SHAS on 
behalf of Labor, submitted the coalition agreement with SHAS as 
well as the letter to Rabbi 'Ovadya Yosef to the Knesset's table. 

</TEXT>

