<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Jewish Underground Issues Ultimatum to Rabin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1803111094 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 18 Mar 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> TA1803111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by New York correspondent Tzadoq Yehezqeli] </F>
  [Text] Kahana Hay activists have threatened attacks along 
the lines of the Hebron massacre if the Israeli Government does 
not revoke its decision to outlaw their organization. 
  In a statement delivered over the telephone to the local 
YEDI'OT AHARONOT offices on behalf of the organization, which is 
now calling itself "The Unified Command of the Global Uprising," 
the callers mentioned the existence of an underground group for 
the first time. 
  The message said that if the Rabin government does not 
accept 
their ultimatum by Lag B'Omer (29 April), the "`Unit of the God 
of Vengeance,' the military arm of the unified Jewish uprising, 
will follow the example set by the hero and martyr Barukh 
Goldstein." The message also stated that the organization would 
launch violent activities even earlier "if Rabin increases his 
persecution of us or if the Jewish settlers are evacuated from 
Hebron." The group also demanded the immediate release of 
Binyamin Ze'ev Kahana, the leader of Kahana Hay. 
  The sources who delivered the message clarified that the 
attacks would be carried out only against Arabs, not Jews. The 
message also stated that if the ultimatum is rejected, the Arabs 
"will have no respite in this country and the ground will burn 
under their feet day and night, in the streets, their homes, and 
the mosques." 
  According to the callers, supporters of the movement have 
flown to Israel from Europe over the past few days and are now 
operating clandestine cells. 

</TEXT>

