<H3> <TI>   Reports, Commentaries Note Clinton-Rabin Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Shar' Reacts to Meetings </H4>
<F P=102> NC1703183694 London MBC Television in Arabic 1800 GMT 17 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703183694 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Anis Abu-al-'Ila in Bonn] </F>
  [Excerpt] In the first official reaction to statements made 
yesterday by U.S. President Bill Clinton and Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin on the developments of peace in the 
Middle East, Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' said in an 
exclusive statement to the MBC: 
  [Begin al-Shar' recording] The requirements of peace are 
well 
known: Full [Israeli] withdrawal and implementation of Security 
Council Resolutions 242, 338, and 425. For security and 
stability to be achieved in the region, the peace process must 
be comprehensive. Otherwise, it remains merely talk that will 
not produce concrete results; on the contrary, using hollow 
expressions about peace without real results will lead to 
terrorism and violence, as happened in the massacre at the holy 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque. [end recording] 
  The statement was given during al-Shar's current three-day 
visit to Bonn. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

