meeting to prepare the warring parties in the Sudan to accept 
the idea of negotiated settlement of their long-drawn conflict. 
They also discussed other procedural matters of the peace 
negotiations. 
  The IGADD [Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and 
Development] committee on peace talks on the Sudan is to 
officially launch the talks later this afternoon. 

