<H3> <TI>   Groups, Officials View Clinton's Jerusalem Remarks </TI></H3>
<H4>   NPUG Denounces Comment </H4>
<F P=102> NC1703165594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1605 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1703165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 17 Mar (MENA)--The National Progressive 
Unionist Grouping [NPUG] party has denounced the statement 
attributed to U.S. President Bill Clinton that his country 
considers unified Jerusalem with its Eastern and Western sectors 
the capital of Israel. 
  In a statement it issued today, the NPUG notes with deepest 
feelings of resentment that this U.S. statement in support of 
the policy of aggression and the annexation of the occupied 
territories comes at a time when world public opinion is 
unanimously condemning the criminal massacre that Israel 
committed at the al-Ibrahimi Mosque. 
  The NPUG called on the Arab League and the Islamic 
Conference 
Organization to adopt a firm stand on this new escalation of the 
attacks on the rights and dignities of the Arabs and Muslims. 

