<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Meets Vorontsov, Other Security Council Envoys </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1703210894 Baghdad INA in Arabic 2042 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1703210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, 17 Mar (INA) -- Deputy Prime 
Minister Tariq 'Aziz met with a number of ambassadors who are 
members of the UN Security Council today. 
  He met at his place of residence with Yuliy Vorontsov, 
Russia's permanent UN Security Council member. He also met 
separately with Brazilian envoy Ronaldo Mota Sardenberg and New 
Zealand envoy [name indistinct]. 
  Tariq 'Aziz is scheduled to meet later today with other UN 
Security Council envoys before he meets with UN Special 
Commission Chairman Rolf Ekeus at his place of residence today, 
Thursday. 

