<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Meets Vatican Foreign Affairs Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803094794 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0600 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Yasir 'Arafat has renewed the PLO's 
appeal to the co-sponsors of the peace conference and the 
members of the Security Council to respond to the Palestinian 
people's request for international protection in the occupied 
territories. 'Arafat renewed this appeal when he received 
Jean-Louis Tauran, official in charge of foreign affairs at the 
Vatican, in Tunis yesterday. 
  The Palestinian president also insisted on the need for the 
Security Council to adopt a resolution condemning the massacre 
at the Tomb of the Patriarchs and providing international 
protection for the Palestinian people. In reply to a question 
on the Palestinian response to President Clinton's call for a 
resumption of talks, 'Arafat said that he wants a frank reply 
before making any answer on the Palestinian position on this 
matter. 
  The Palestinian news agency reported yesterday evening that 
President 'Arafat and the Vatican envoy discussed ways of 
strengthening relations between the Palestinians and the Vatican 
and providing international protection for the Palestinian 
people from the attacks and massacres perpetrated by Israeli 
settlers. They also discussed the role of the Vatican in 
supporting the peace process on the basis of safeguarding 
Palestinian rights, particularly the issue of holy Jerusalem, 
which is important to Palestinians, Arabs, Muslims, and 
Christians alike. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

