<H3> <TI>   Hamas Action in Territories Only `Matter of Time' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1703170994 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 17 Mar 94 p3 </F>
<F P=103> PM1703170994 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Hamas: Al-Qassam Squads Will Carry </F>
Out Their Threats"] 
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] sources have stated that the 'Izz-al-Din 
al-Qassam Squads intend to carry out their threats "against the 
occupation presence in the occupied territories" and emphasized 
that implementation of such operations is only a matter of time. 
  The sources made these comments to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT after 
the expiry of Hamas' deadline to the Jewish settlers and 
occupation forces, after which it said it would deal painful 
retaliatory blows to them. It is believed, however, that the 
tightened measures and precautions have made it difficult to 
carry out such operations, particularly as the Israeli 
leadership has taken into consideration the possibility of such 
operations by the 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam Squads -- the military 
wing of Hamas -- to avenge the martyrs of al-Ibrahimi Mosque in 
Hebron. 

</TEXT>

