<H3> <TI>   Rabin, 'Arafat Discuss Resumption of Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1803151694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 18 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1803151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This afternoon, Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and 
Yasir 'Arafat spoke on the phone for 15 minutes. They discussed 
the possibility of resuming the peace talks. Our correspondent 
Shlomo Raz reports that Mr. Rabin initiated the conversation. 
It appears that no Jewish site in Hebron will be evacuated at 
this time. 
  Minister Moshe Shahal estimated today that the talks between 
the PLO and Israel will resume before the Passover holidays 
[starting on 27 March]. Regarding the Waqf decision to ban the 
entry of non-Muslims to the Temple Mount, Minister Shahal said 
that Israel will not accept the Waqf decision, but stressed that 
such disagreements are better solved through silent diplomacy. 

</TEXT>

