<H3> <TI>   Ayatollah Jannati Delivers Friday Prayers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803115594 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] On the eve of the Iranian new year, and on the 
last Friday of 1372 [year ending 20 March], the 
political-religious rites of Friday prayers were staged 
throughout the country today, with the extensive participation 
of the worshiping masses. In Tehran, the Friday prayers were led 
by Ayatollah Ahmad Jannati. 
  The acting Friday prayer leader of Tehran expressed 
congratulations on the occasions of the blessed 'Id al-Fitr and 
the auspicious new year. He stressed that people should use 
such occasions in order to perform good deeds, in particular 
deeds such as giving charity and aid to the poor and the 
underprivileged. [passage omitted] 
  In his second sermon, Ayatollah Jannati thanked the Majles 
for its careful, timely, and skillful debate on the budget bill. 
He then referred to the anniversary of the Halabjah tragedy and 
the silence of international forums, in particular the so-called 
defenders of human rights, on that and other tragedies, such as 
the recent atrocity at the Hebron mosque and the continuing 
criminal acts in Bosnia-Herzegovina. He said: These realities 
show that what is at present being said in the West about human 
rights is nothing but a political ploy. This ploy, however, is 
now old and rotten, and it should be clear to every one now that 
the greatest violator of human rights in the world is in fact 
America. 
  He stressed: Such insinuations do not, and will never, have 
any effect whatsoever on the resolute will of the Muslim nation 
of Iran, and the struggle of the resilient nation of Iran 
against global arrogance will continue under the wise leadership 
of His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

