<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Hirawi on Need To Implement Resolution 425 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903152194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1400 GMT 19 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1903152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the 16th anniversary of Security Council 
Resolution 425, President Ilyas al-Hirawi has emphasized that 
Lebanon looks to the UN to help everybody implement the 
international resolutions. Lebanon, he added, has proved its 
ability to overcome its crisis and is able to extend the state's 
authority to every inch of its territory. 
  President al-Hirawi added that Lebanon, which seeks UN help 
to safeguard its inalienable rights, rejects violence as a way 
of resolving crises just as it rejects infringement of its 
national dignity and legitimate rights. He added: Resolution 
425 did not give us a right we were not entitled to. Rather, it 
reaffirmed our sacred right to have our sovereignty respected. 
  The president added: Let Israel withdraw from our land and 
the state will take it upon itself to maintain stability there. 
He stressed the need for alertness and solidarity with our 
brothers and cooperation with our friends to secure the 
implementation of the international resolutions, chiefly 
Resolution 425. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

