<H3> <TI>   Ja'ja' Denies Link to Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2003075694 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0545 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2003075694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a statement to AL-HAYAH newspaper, Dr. Samir 
Ja'ja' said: I again reject any direct or indirect hints or 
accusations of the Lebanese forces for bombing the Sayyidat 
al-Najat Church. He said that those who make these accusations 
are unscrupulous criminals who want to cover up their actions by 
accusing us. These accusations are rumors and are not based on 
evidence [words indistinct]. 
  Ja'ja' said that under the pretext of investigations, an 
organized political campaign of suppression is launched. The 
campaign is now aimed against the Lebanese forces and it will be 
aimed against other parties tomorrow. 
  According to press reports, Dr. Ja'ja' made two telephone 
calls to President Ilyas al-Hirawi and Chamber of Deputies 
Speaker Nabih Birri inquiring about the reasons for the raids on 
the Lebanese Forces centers and requesting them to intercede to 
stop this campaign. 

