<H3> <TI>   New Chairman for Shiite Council Elected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1803110094 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1000 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1803110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Higher Islamic Shiite Council held a meeting 
at its temporary headquarters in Tallat al-Khayyat this morning 
and elected Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams-al-Din council chairman, 
succeeding Shaykh Musa al-Sar, the council's founder [who 
disappeared during a visit to Libya in August 1978]. Shaykh 
Shams-al-Din has been deputy chairman of the council since 1974. 
  The council members also elected Ja'farite Mufti 
'Abd-al-Amir 
Qabalan as first deputy chairman and Dr. 'Adnan Haydar as second 
deputy chairman. Some 46 of the council's 48 members attended 
the session. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

