<H3> <TI>   President Reelected With 99 Percent of Votes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103124394 Tunis Tunis-7 Television in Arabic 1207 GMT 21 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunis-7 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Successive announcements have been made since dawn 
today on the results of the presidential and legislative 
elections that took place yesterday, Sunday. Interior Minister 
Abdallah Kallel will officially announce the results at a news 
conference this afternoon. As a reminder, the turnout at these 
elections was unparalleled with more than 90 percent of voters, 
men, and women, taking part in the vote in the 25 electoral 
districts. The presidential elections were marked by an 
absolute popular plebiscite for President Zine El Abidine Ben 
Ali; the percentage of the vote for President Zine El Abidine 
Ben Ali exeeded 99 percent and this rate reached 100 percent in 
Tataouine. 
  As for the legislative elections, the lists of the 
Democratic 
Constitutional Rally won in all districts with an extremely high 
percentage of votes, but these results will assuredly lead to 
the entry of the other parties into the chamber of deputies for 
the first time in the history of Tunisia due to the amendment to 
the electoral code, which guarantees the presence of these 
parties in parliament. 

</TEXT>

