<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Warns Dostam Against Shelling Kabul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1803155494 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1803155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to reports from Afghanistan, there has 
been sporadic rocket firing on the capital, Kabul, from this 
morning. The Afghan Defense Ministry has recently warned that if 
the Dostam militia resorts to shelling Kabul, the government air 
force will take retaliatory action and the militia bases in and 
around Mazar-e Sharif will come under air strikes. However, 
there has been no report of any aerial action so far. Reports 
also say that there has been continuous exchange of artillery 
and rocket fire between rival factions in the northern province 
of Baghlan. 

</TEXT>

