<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Kuwait, 21 March -- In a press statement 
published here today, Minister of State for Cabinet Affairs 
'Abd-al-'Aziz al- Dakhil has denied reports of the existence of 
an Iraqi offer to exchange Kuwaiti prisoners still in the Iraqi 
regime's prisons for 11 Iraqis being tried in Kuwait charged 
with attempting to assassinate former American President George 
Bush. The newspaper AL-ANBA quoted the minister of state for 
cabinet affairs as saying that the State of Kuwait "has not and 
will not agree to this type of maneuvering and trickery, which 
is undertaken by the Baghdad regime from time to time to create 
a stir and give the international community the impression that 
it is seeking to find stability in the region." He pointed out 
that "the aim behind this attempt is to lift the economic 
sanctions that have been imposed on Iraq for some time now." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

