<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Riyadh, March 18, SPA -- Saudi papers on Friday 
tackled a number of regional and international topics. 
  Commenting on the development of the peace process in the 
Middle East following the vicious massacre of Hebron last month, 
the Jeddah-based AL-MADINAH cited statements made recently by 
the Israeli Prime Minister Rabin and a high-ranking Israeli 
general and said the statements made it clear that Israel does 
not sincerely interest in peace and talking about peace is just 
for local consumption and for wasting time. [passage omitted] 
  For its part, 'UKAZ, also published in Jeddah, expressed 
surprise on the American latest positions on the peace process 
in the Middle East and said the American stand would not remove 
obstacles that hinder realisation of a peaceful settlement. 
  The paper criticized the U.S. attempts to prevent the 
Security Council from making a resolution to denounce the 
massacre of Hebron. It also deplored a statement attributed to 
President Clinton recently on the status of al-Quds [Jerusalem] 
as an insult for the Arab and Moslim people. 
  The paper cited the importance of an international 
protection 
for the residents of the occupied lands before making any 
breakthrough in peace talks. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

