<H3> <TI>   Basindawah Briefs Foreign Envoys on Crisis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2003130194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2003130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister brother Muhammad Salim Basindwah 
received a number of friendly states' ambassadors in Sanaa at 
noon today. He briefed them on the situation in Yemen as a 
result of the current political crisis. He expressed the thanks 
of the president, leadership, government, and people of Yemen 
for their support for Yemen's unity and democracy, for their 
interest in our country's security, safety, and stability, and 
for their respective countries' sincere and unbiased stands on 
the crisis. 
  He said he appreciated all friends' sincere efforts to 
contain the crisis, especially those that are being exerted by 
the United States. He emphasized the call for their respective 
countries to deal directly with the Foreign Ministry in its 
capacity as our country's main channel of contact and 
representative of the constitutional legitimate authority of the 
Republic of Yemen. 

</TEXT>

