<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suspects in 1993 Coup Attempt Reportedly Tortured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1703184694 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 17 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Libyan opposition group has announced that the 
Libyan (?intelligence service) tortured Libyan Army officers who 
had been involved in an unsuccessful bid to overthrow the regime 
and forced them to appear on television to publicly confess that 
they had been spying for the United States. 
  A spokesman for the Libyan National Salvation Front [words 
indistinct] that Libyan leader Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi continued 
to deny there had been a rebellion even though Arab diplomatic 
sources in Libya assert that a rebellion really did occur. 
  At the time of the rebellion, press sources said it was 
organized by Islamic hardliners among the Army officers. These 
sources said the rebellion started on 11 October 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

