<H3> <TI>   Source on `Contacts' With U.S. on UN Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1803181294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1720 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1803181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Harare, 18 Mar (MENA)--An official Egyptian source 
stated that Egypt continues its contacts with the United States 
on the adoption of a Security Council resolution condemning "the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre" on 15 Ramadan, with the aim of 
resuming the peace negotiations between the Israelis and 
Palestinians, and on the other tracks. In a statement to MENA 
in Harare today, the source said the issuance of such a 
resolution by the Security Council would reassure the PLO about 
the protection and security of the Palestinian people in the 
occupied Arab territories. He noted that a U.S. veto of such a 
resolution would be an obstacle to the peace process. 

