<H3> <TI>   Islamic Group Claims Responsibility for Bank Blast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2003185094 London MBC Television in Arabic 1800 GMT 20 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2003185094 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Group in Egypt has claimed 
responsibility for detonating a bomb in front of a Cairo bank 
yesterday, which wounded one person and caused severe property 
damage to the building. The Islamic Group has launched more 
than nine bomb attacks against Egyptian and foreign banks. 
  In a statement issued today, it warned people who frequent 
banks of similar attacks. The statement added that yesterday's 
explosion in front of a building housing the Misr-America 
International Bank had come in revenge for the execution of two 
[Army] officers on Thursday on charges of attempting to 
assassinate Egyptian President Husni Mubarak during a visit to 
the Sidi Barrani base at the Egyptian-Libyan border in November. 

</TEXT>

