<H4>   Arab League Envoy Comments </H4>
<F P=102> NC2003150994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1430 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2003150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Mar (MENA)--Dr. Nabil Najm, Iraqi 
permanent delegate to the Arab League, has stated that 
yesterday's renewal of sanctions on Iraq will have a tremendous 
effect on the Iraqi people and will cause more deaths among the 
Iraqi women, children, and patients. 
  In a statement here today, Dr. Najm described this step as 
one that "will not help stability in the region" and denounced 
what he called "the double standards adopted by the Security 
Council on Arab issues." 
  The Iraqi delegate denied that Iraq had proposed to swap 
some 
Kuwaiti detainees with some Iraqi defendants detained in Kuwaiti 
prisons on charges of attempting to assassinate former U.S. 
President George Bush. He added that this is completely untrue 
because Iraq has no Kuwaiti detainees. 

</TEXT>

