<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   CIA Reportedly Funding Secular Press in Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1903162494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1530 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1903162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] America's intelligence and spying agency, the CIA, 
in order to encourage the press to increase their propaganda 
attacks on Islam, has provided $35 million of financial aid to 
the writers of the secular press in Turkey. 
  (BIKEK) newspaper, published in Istanbul, carries this 
report 
in today's edition, adding that, by making use of the CIA's 
financial assistance and the support of Western countries, 
Turkey's secular newspapers have started an extensive propaganda 
campaign among Turkey's secular circles against the 
Islamic-leaning Rafah [Prosperity] party. 

</TEXT>

