<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Welcomes UN Security Council Resolution 904 </TI></H3>
<H4>   'Abd-Rabbuh: Resolution Helps Process </H4>
<F P=102> JN1903104094 Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network in 
Arabic 0930 GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1903104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, PLO Executive Committee member, 
has said that the PLO welcomes the UN Security Council 
resolution which denounced the al-Ibrahimi Mosque Massacre in 
Hebron and regards it a step toward helping resume the peace 
process. 
  In a statement to REUTER, 'Abd-Rabbuh said that the PLO will 
receive an Israeli delegation within the next few days to 
discuss measures that will provide security for Palestinians in 
the occupied territory. 'Abd-Rabbuh added that PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat has no plans to meet with Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres in Cairo tomorrow, as was reported earlier. 
  'Abd-Rabbuh said that what is important for Palestinians is 
to implement the UN Security Council resolution on the Hebron 
massacre and for the Israeli Government to adopt full and 
tangible measures in this regard. 'Abd-Rabbuh said that the 
U.S. coordinator, Dennis Ross, proposed such a meeting in a 
telephone call to 'Arafat last Thursday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

