<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Groups React to UN Resolution 904 </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hamas: Resolution `Does Not Suffice' </H4>
<F P=102> TA1903122194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 19 
mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1903122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] has announced 
it rejects UN Security Council Resolution number 904 on the 
Hebron massacre because it does not denounce the Zionist entity. 
In a statement disseminated in the territories today, Hamas 
spokesman Ibrahim Ghawshah says the UN resolution does not 
suffice, because it does not call for the evacuation of the 
settlers from Hebron and for disarming them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

