<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Groups React to UN Resolution 904 </TI></H3>
<H4>   DFLP Criticizes Hebron Resolution </H4>
<F P=102> JN1903125094 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 19 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1903125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine 
[DFLP] regards the new U.S. attitude toward the UN Security 
Council resolution as a disturbing retreat from the stands 
adopted by previous U.S. Administrations. The front called 
Resolution No. 904 weak and colorless with no firm decisions on 
protecting the Palestinian people. 
  The Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas, rejected the 
resolution and considered it insufficient and incomplete. Hamas 
voiced its disappointment with the stands of the Arab sides, 
including that of the PLO. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

