<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Reacts to UN Hebron Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1903052194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 19 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1903052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry in Jerusalem issued the 
following statement in response to the UN Security Council 
resolution: Israel believes that the best way to promote peace 
and security between Israelis and Palestinians is by resuming 
and accelerating negotiations on the implementation of the 
Declaration of Principles [DOP] on Gaza and Jericho. In regard 
to the Security Council resolution, Israel hopes it will pave 
the way for the resumption of these talks. Israel was first to 
condemn the horrendous massacre in Hebron and will continue to 
take decisive action against extremists and dangerous elements. 
Israel will encourage any measures to restore stability in the 
territories -- as far as they are in conformity with the DOP -- 
and do its utmost to carry out its responsibility for the 
security of all Arabs and Israelis in the territories. Finally, 
Israel's position on Jerusalem is well known: Jerusalem is and 
will be the united capital of Israel. Any reference to it as 
part of the territories is unacceptable. 

</TEXT>

