<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mayor Disappointed by U.S. Vote on UN Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2003172294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1600 GMT 20 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2003172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert says the U.S. vote on 
the UN resolution condemning the Hebron massacre has raised 
false expectations among Palestinians regarding the future of 
Jerusalem, and will create obstacles to the peace process. 
  In a letter to President Bill Clinton, Olmert said he was 
disappointed that the U.S. did not veto the Security Council 
resolution, which contains references to East Jerusalem as part 
of the occupied territories. The United States voted in support 
of the resolution, but abstained on citations referring to the 
status of Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

