<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kakh Leader Reportedly To Surrender </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2003084894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 20 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2003084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Barukh Marzel has announced that he will turn 
himself in through the mediation of several Knesset members 
[MK's]. This is because, among other reasons, he fears that the 
authorities will use firearms during his arrest. In a letter 
sent to his wife, Marzel asserted that he is unarmed and has no 
intention of resisting arrest. 
  Our correspondent Gil Litman reports that Marzel, one of the 
leaders of the Kakh movement, has been in hiding from the police 
for several weeks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

