<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   King To Discuss Yemen With Omani Sultan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2103082994 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0500 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2103082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn will pay a visit to the 
Sultanate of Oman today. This will be followed by a visit to 
the State of Qatar on Wednesday [23 March] in order to hold 
consultations and coordination with the leaders of both 
fraternal countries. 
  In a statement to AFP, his majesty added that during his 
visit to Oman he will discuss with His Majesty Sultan Qabus 
Bin-Sa'id the Yemeni accord document signed in Amman on 20 
February. His majesty pointed out that there will also be an 
assessment of the joint efforts regarding what was achieved and 
the situation in the future; in other words, whether or not to 
continue [these efforts] or have the kinsfolk and brothers in 
Yemen tackle their matters and situation [internally]. 
  His majesty regarded his visit to Qatar as heralding the 
resumption of relations, which were always strong and based on 
confidence and amity. He pointed out that the visit comes after 
a long cessation of such fraternal visits. 

</TEXT>

